<week><weekid>2</weekid>
<weekname>Pre-class asynchronous </weekname>
<node><name>Prepare and Assign Material</name>
<id>14</id>
<lefticon>undefined</lefticon>
<righticon>orchestration</righticon>
<column>OOCI</column>
<textHTML>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prepare and assign material for students to complete prior to the synchronous class.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Assign students to groups of 4-6. Each group will be assigned a different role. Refer to a &lt;a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Zk7eFjRUfLblpkro9OsbsQfIG3bvBeY-BPbwy05Sl2c/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank"&gt;list of possible roles&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Optional: Consider group dynamics when assigning groups. This is a great opportunity to get different students working together.&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>160</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
<node><name>Read or Watch Assigned Material</name>
<id>7</id>
<lefticon>solo</lefticon>
<righticon>reading</righticon>
<column>OOC</column>
<textHTML>&lt;p&gt;Read or watch assigned material to prepare for online class, while focusing on instructions for the assigned role.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note: To communicate and assign material, use your course page (i.e., course management system e.g., &lt;a href="https://www.dawsoncollege.qc.ca/information-systems-and-technology/articles/lea/" target="_blank"&gt;LEA&lt;/a&gt;, Moodle)&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>99</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
</week>
<week><weekid>4</weekid>
<weekname>Online class synchronous activity </weekname>
<node><name>Give Lecture and Divide Groups</name>
<id>8</id>
<lefticon>undefined</lefticon>
<righticon>orchestration</righticon>
<column>ICI</column>
<textHTML>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Begin class with a mini lecture: What you want students to do and what type of resource you want them to generate.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Divide class into their pre-assigned groups, based on their pre-assigned roles.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;During group work (stage 1) check in with each group to facilitate progress and group discussion (where needed).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use a web conferencing tool (i.e .Zoom). Zoom can work as a stand alone or within a LMS (e.g., Moodle, LEA). Students can be assigned to breakout rooms for group work.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use a whiteboard to create a concept map with your students (e.g. Zoom whiteboard feature)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If assigning PDF materials, consider using &lt;a href="https://perusall.com/" target="_blank"&gt;Persusall&lt;/a&gt;--a free online tool allows groups to collaboratively annotate a PDF&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>338</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
<node><name>Discuss Insights</name>
<id>9</id>
<lefticon>group</lefticon>
<righticon>discuss</righticon>
<column>ICS</column>
<textHTML>&lt;p&gt;Stage 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Review instructions and discuss the role their group has been assigned (e.g. role of source evaluator).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Share, in a go-around, one insight about the material (e.g., as source evaluators, one student comments on author's credibility, another student comments on methodologies used to collect data, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Option: Do a second go-around to see if there are more insights that were not mentioned.&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>188</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
<node><name>Create Resource</name>
<id>28</id>
<lefticon>group</lefticon>
<righticon>create</righticon>
<column>ICS</column>
<textHTML>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Consolidate expertise (e.g., what are the top 2-3 strengths and weaknesses of this source)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create a resource that includes discussion questions. Each group member becomes an expert and should have access to the record for their individual presentation during their stage 2 group work.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note: Students can collaborate and consolidate with online collaborative tools: Google doc, Span workspace canvas, or &lt;a href="https://maasd.edublogs.org/smart-board/jigsaw/" target="_blank"&gt;Smart Notebook&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>205</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
<node><name>Feedback and reassign new groups </name>
<id>10</id>
<lefticon>undefined</lefticon>
<righticon>orchestration</righticon>
<column>ICI</column>
<textHTML>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Reconvene class and provide feedback on how 1st breakout groups worked&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Outline stage 2 expectations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Reassign students into new groups for stage 2. Ensure new groups are composed of different role experts.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;During group work, check in with each group to facilitate progress and group discussion (where needed).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note: &lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Option: If some groups finish early, assign them another role to the group, or prompt them with further discussion questions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Option: Ask each group, as a roundtable of experts, to come up with arguments/ positions/ recommendations related to topics based on the material.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>315</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
<node><name>Present and Discuss Material</name>
<id>11</id>
<lefticon>group</lefticon>
<righticon>present</righticon>
<column>ICS</column>
<textHTML>&lt;p&gt;Stage 2&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Explain, in a go-around, the role and present consolidated expertise on the material&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Discuss material as a group. Experts take turns posing questions to the rest of the group&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Option: Each group chooses an ambassador to report during the debrief.&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>160</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
<node><name>Debrief, Review, and Consolidate</name>
<id>12</id>
<lefticon>undefined</lefticon>
<righticon>orchestration</righticon>
<column>ICI</column>
<textHTML>&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Reconvene the class&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Facilitate students sharing and debriefing highlights, conclusions, challenges or further questions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Review material, connect back to learning goals, draw important links and consolidate the top 3-4 central ideas that students are expected to walk away with from the lesson.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Option: Using a &lt;a href="https://www.saltise.ca/strategy/concept-mapping/" target="_blank"&gt;concept map&lt;/a&gt; could visually help bring together all of the ideas emerging from the groups.&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
<linkedwf>undefined</linkedwf>
<textheight>202</textheight>
<isdropped>true</isdropped>
</node>
